text:
East 177th Street, north side, west from Watson (right) to Castle Hill Aves. The two frame houses, on the extreme right, face on the north side of Watson Ave. Also shown is a general view in a northeasterly direction as seen from the S.E. corner of Castle Hill and Watson Aves.

May 1926.

Brown Brothers.

East 177th Street, east from Watson Ave. Also shown is a general view northeastward as seen from the S.E. corner of Castle Hill and Watson Aves. In front of the gas tank of the Bronx Gas and Electric Company are three units of the German Odd Fellows Home.

May 1926.

Brown Brothers.

original_title: Bronx: Castle Hill Avenue - Watson Avenue
text:
(1)
Castle Hill Avenue, at the S.W. corner of Watson Avenue, showing the Holy Family Roman Catholic Church and the rectory. The view is across E. 177th Street.
July 1, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NI2 i S 1E
(2)
Another view of the rectory and church, viewed south along the avenue from Blackrock Avenue.
May 10, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
0 g 33'
